<br>
Anyway, I've noticed that no one spends any time in the Taverns.  None.  Zilch.  We're all too busy running here or there, doing things for our Guilds or following up on a quest or trying to level or trying to acquire skills.<br>
<br>
Bards, you have a great opportunity to encourage meaningful roleplay.  Tell stories of the adventures you've been on.<br>
<br>
Let people know you're doing this; I don't think the &quot;roleplay nazis&quot; or anyone else would object to using /shout or /auction to let people know your holding a concert.  The few times I did this, I drew between three and eight people; furthermore, those people got to know each other better.<br>
<br>
(Personally, I think other classes could do some similar things: Clerics preaching in the churches or holding holiday celebrations, Druids holding celebrations and performing rituals at the Druid Rings, and so forth.)<br>
<br>
...just a thought, anyway...<br>
<br>
